snippet.textDisplay:
Yew! Go the Booyz! Another great team performance with great positional play n everyone awake n switched on n at the top of there game. A really professional  n clinical team performance n we had to be as Wolves turned up to play n were on it as well, even though Liverpool dominated the 1st half n as much as it doesn`t matter or figure much over all, that we had most of the Possession.


Right, straight into the useless VAR let`s completely kill football Tech n Nuno n Wolves Maaaa! life is unfair can you change my nappy hissy fit!  Yes it was handball against van Dijk as the ball clearly bounces up n rebounds of the inside of his upper arm n Wolves should of had a free kick...yet at the time the Wolves player standing near van Dijk saw it n didn`t appeal for hand ball n neither did any other Wolves player on the pitch or Nuno or Anyone from the Wolves sideline in that moment!...That van Dijk handled the ball!...It wasn`t handball from Lallana, he clearly uses his shoulder to pass the ball to Mane who was clearly onside n scores the goal.


Wolves, you missed the moment! No point whinging n vitching once the goal is scored about what you didn`t whinge n vitch about moments earlier when the actual handball with van Dijk, happened n even though at half time, VAR checked the van Dijk handball n said it was inconclusive, which is absolute rubbish, it was clearly handball! All the same, if you want to get down to details n BS, there were at least 3 or 4 Wolves handballs in this match that were not given n in every other ferken match ever played, whether a goal was scored in a later phase or not!


As well as the Wolves free kick that was given, early in the 2nd half when Jonny made the most of Robbo`s slightest touch on his back n Jonny dramatically flew through the Air as if Robbo took a ferken run up n planted one in the middle of his back with all that he could hit him with!  Then at another stage in the 2nd half, Jonny slightly touches the back of Mane who goes down in the box, yet no in direct free kick or penalty given???? Ferken if`s buts n maybe`s!...Ferken really Wolves!?


Carrying on n Crying so much over spilt milk, just makes Nuno n Wolves look like kids who had there toys taken away n having a hissy fit because of it. Also where do you get off whinging n vitching about VAR n the referee missing that one n not getting it right, then whinge n vitch at VAR n the referee minutes later for getting it mm perfect n right!...with the Jonny, Wolves offside to disallow Neto`s goal?! You can`t have it both ways Wolves!


You can cry Wolves as much as you like n say why Wolves all the time n the busy football calendar is unfair as well, like you do, the fact is!....the busy football calendar is the same for every premier league team, Liverpool have already played 34 games in all competitions this season ( the highest in the premier league) n Wolves playing 32 ( the 2nd highest in the premier league) As well, Jonny was offside by mm`s...yes no one likes it ( except me n the rest of Liverpool in this moment :)!


Just in this past weekend alone it was the same in 3 other premier league matches,  Norwich City vs Spurs, Brighton vs Bournemouth n Crystal Palace vs Southampton, with goals being ruled out by mm`s. It`s a regular thing now week in n week out.


Yes, as I said, no one likes it n in a perfect world it should of been 1-1 at half time, even the Liverpool players had accepted it n were walking back to half way to restart the match.
The reality is, you can whinge n vitch about VAR to the cows come ferken home! Doesn`t change it or the reality! As much as everyone hates it n that VAR is killing the game of football! We are stuck with the verken thing n untouchable referees until the powers that be in the premier league wake up to how crap it all is n change it!


It happened to Wolves in this game n it`s happened to Liverpool n every other team in the premier league at some point in the past n will again in the future...so suck it up n get the ferk on with it Nuno n Wolves or cry into your tissues n wear your nappies?!...Either way it doesn`t change what is!...in this match!, All at Wolves!...ignored van Dijk`s handball until after the fact n then whinged n vitched about it when Mane scored a legitimate goal n then you whinged at VAR for getting it right with Jonny`s offside goal! What can I say?...oh I know!...it ferken sux to be you!....Grow the ferk up n build a bridge n get the ferk over it n get the ferk on with it!


Anyway...moving on, once Wolves got over there 1st half life isn`t fair, where`s my nappy hissy fit, it was a really good quality 2nd half from both teams with shared n even possession, with Liverpool pretty much focusing on n suceeding in containing Wolves to mainly mid field play n action n doing what was needed in defence when Wolves got near our 18 yrd box n keeping speed machine Traore really quite when he came on n limiting him to just one or two half decent excursions n crosses down our left wing, forcing Traore to go central more often to chase the ball, with limited success.


Which meant Wolves, therefore, also limited Trent n Robbo`s deep runs n crosses into Wolves half, which starved our front three of much Wolves goal mouth play n action. Liverpool have played Wolves 10 times now in our history n we have won all 10, even though this was a really intense n high quality match from both sides, especially in the 2nd half n a really good test for Liverpool, again we came through with flying colours.


As well as Wolves played in the 2nd half, it was pretty much contained in the midfield n Wolves never really looked like cracking Liverpool's defence n getting there equaliser, even though in the last minutes of the match, Wolves had 3 good opportunities to level it, they didn`t take those chances, Sux to be Wolves!


They certainly never looked like they would dominate Liverpool at any stage of the match n go on n win it. With Klopp weaving his magic n Liverpool`s level of play easily dealing with whatever Wolves tried to throw at us...hissy fits, quality play n all...in the end a fairly routine n dominant display by the Reds over all, against an up for it n quality Wolves team, despite there 1st half hissy fit. With Liverpool doing what we have done all season!...Doing what`s needed n winning football matches! Enfield is a Fortress! 50 home games unbeaten! Get that into you! Yew Go the Booyz!


We march on to the 2nd half of the season, unbeaten in the 1st half of the season! Congratulations n Happy New Year to All our Liverpool Family! We are Liverpool! Go the Booyz! YNWA!
